Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setEcoMode(25.10)                                            setEcoMode(25.10)

Name
       setEcoMode   -   Controls  certain  behaviors  of  the  ecoAddRepeater,
       ecoChangeCell, and ecoDeleteRepeater ECO commands

Syntax
       setEcoMode

       [-help]

       [-addPortAsNeeded {true|false}]

       [-batchMode {true|false}]

       [-reset]

       [-honorDontTouch {true|false}]

       [-honorDontUse {true|false}]

       [-honorFixedNetWire {true|false}]

       [-honorFixedStatus {true|false}]

       [-honorPowerIntent {true|false}]

       [-inheritNetAttr {true|false}]

       [-LEQCheck {true|false}]

       [-modifyOnlyLayers <bottom_layer>:<top_layer>]

       [-prefixName <prefix>]

       [-preserveModuleFunction {true|false}]

       [-refinePlace {true|false}]

       [-spreadInverter {true|false}]e

       [-updateTiming {true|false}]

       [-delayCalcEffort <effort_level>]

       Controls certain behaviors of the  ecoAddRepeater,  ecoChangeCell,  and
       ecoDeleteRepeater ECO commands.

       Use the getEcoMode command to return the current settings for the setE-
       coMode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setEcoMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man setEcoMode.

       -addPortAsNeeded {true|false}
              Controls whether interactive ECO adds ports to  the  lower-level
              hierarchies  of the design. It only works during interactive ECO
              and overwrites the value of setOptMode -addPortAsNeeded for  the
              ECO  commands,  ecoAddRepeater,  ecoChangeCell, and ecoDeleteRe-
              peater.

              Default: true

       -batchMode {true|false}
              Speeds up the runtime in case the user performs lots of interac-
              tive ECO operations. When the  user  specifies  batchMode  true,
              various  ECO operations are performed in a batch and initializa-
              tion steps are not performed for every ECO  call.  In  addition,
              updating  timing  is  performed only once for all the ECO opera-
              tions. Tool will only perform timing initialization at the first
              ECO command in the batch mode and timing update at the  time  of
              exiting  the batchMode. User needs to specify batchMode false to
              exit the batchMode.

              The batch mode is activated by setEcoMode  -batchMode  true  and
              exited by setEcoMode -batchMode false, and only ecoAddRepeater ,
              ecoDeleteRepeater  and  ecoChangeCell  could be given in between
              setEcoMode -batchMode true and  setEcoMode -batchMode false:

              setEcoMode -batchMode true

              eco commands (ecoAddRepeater, ecoDeleteRepeater, ecoChangeCell)

              setEcoMode -batchMode false

              If a user activates the batch mode, then the user needs  to  re-
              member to exit it. If the user does not exit the batch mode, the
              user might see some unexpected results.

              The refinePlace command will not be called in batchMode. It will
              be  called  when the tool exits the batchMode and if refinePlace
              is set to true.

              All other setEcoMode settings should be made prior to activating
              batch mode. If you would like to change setEcoMode settings, you
              need to exit the batch mode first.

              Note: This option supports all commit ECO  commands.  Evaluation
              commands are not supported.

       -delayCalcEffort  <effort_level>
              Specifies  the  delay  calculation effort level { low | medium |
              high } used in timing update.

              Default: high

       -honorDontTouch {true|false}
              Checks for the don't touch attribute on nets and  instances.  If
              you specify a terminal list, this parameter checks each terminal
              for the don't touch attribute. The ecoAddRepeater command honors
              the  don't  touch  nets. The ecoDeleteRepeater and ecoChangeCell
              commands honor don't touch instances.

              Default: true

       -honorDontUse {true|false}
              Checks for the don't use attribute on cells. The ecoAddRepeater,
              ecoDeleteRepeater, and ecoChangeCell commands  honor  don't  use
              cells.

              Default: true

       -honorFixedNetWire {true|false}
              Checks for fixed net wires.

              It  restricts  the addition or deletion on fixed net so that the
              fixed status of the wires is not altered.

              Default: true

              When -honorFixedNetWire is set to false, ecoAddRepeater can  in-
              sert  a cell on the wires with the FIXED/COVER status and change
              the status of these wires from FIXED/COVER to ROUTED.

       -honorFixedStatus {true|false}
              Does not allow preplaced, fixed instances to be resized.

              Default: true

       -honorPowerIntent {true|false}
              Performs MSV checks during ECO. When set to true:

              * ecoChangeCell does not allow:

                * Resizing a regular cell with an always-on  cell  (and  vice-
                  versa).

                * Resizing with cells belonging to different power domains.

              * ecoAddRepeater does not allow:

                * Adding buffer to a power domain it doesn't belong to.

                * Buffering  a cross power domain net if it can cause MSV vio-
                  lations.

                * Adding a regular buffer to a net that requires an  always-on
                  buffer.

                * Adding an always-on buffer to a net that does not require an
                  always-on buffer.

              * ecoDeleteRepeater  does  not  allow deletion of a buffer or an
                inverter-pair that will cause:

                *
                   A redundant isolation cell.

                *
                   A CPF-constrained net to be deleted.

              Note:  To prevent buffer  insertion  failure  due  to  MSV  con-
              straints, you need to set -honorPowerIntent to false.

              Default: true

       -inheritNetAttr {true | false}
              Inherits the net attribute.

              Default: true

       -LEQCheck {true|false}
              Enables functionality checking when swapping cells. The software
              can swap cells that are logically equivalent.

              When -LEQCheck is true:

              * ecoAddRepeater adds inverter pair if the specified cell is in-
                verter.

              * ecoDeleteRepeater  deletes  inverter pair if the specified in-
                stance is inverter.

              * ecoChangeCell changes cell to another cell type with the  same
                function as long as they have same number of pins.

              When -LEQCheck is set to false:

              * ecoAddRepeater  can add only one single inverter if the speci-
                fied cell is inverter.

              * ecoDeleteRepeater can delete only one single inverter  if  the
                specified instance is inverter.

              * ecoChangeCell can perform nonequivalent cell change as long as
                they have same number of pins.

              Default: true

       -modifyOnlyLayers <bottom_layer>:<top_layer>
              Modifies  routes only on metal layers in this range (both inclu-
              sive).

              Default:""

       -prefixName <prefix>
              Adds a prefix to the inserted cells.

              Default: ECO

              Note: If the prefix name for eco  cells  is  changed  using  the
              -prefixName option, it is not honored when the ECO batch mode is
              turned on.

       -preserveModuleFunction {true|false}
              Determines whether to preserve logical functions at hierarchical
              module  ports.  It  only works for manual ECO commands and over-
              writes the value of setOptMode  -opt_preserve_hpin_function  for
              the    ECO    commands,   ecoAddRepeater,   ecoChangeCell,   and
              ecoDeleteRepeater.

              The setOptMode -preserveModuleFuntion setting overrides  setEco-
              Mode  -preserveModuleFuntion  unless  you explicitly set the eco
              mode.

              Default: false

       -refinePlace {true|false}
              Legalizes placement whenever ecoAddRepeater or ecoChangeCell are
              used. If false, you must run refinePlace after ECO if  you  want
              to legalize placement.

              Note:  Specifying  -refinePlace true can affect performance when
              large numbers of cells are added or modified.

              Default: true

       -reset Resets parameters to their default values. The -reset  parameter
              must  be  the first parameter specified. If you specify reset by
              itself, the software resets all setEcoMode parameters  to  their
              default  values.  If  you  specify  parameters after -reset, the
              software resets only those parameters to their default values.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

       -spreadInverter {true|false}
              Distributes  an  inverter pair evenly between the driver and the
              sink. It works when the buffering nets have only one driver  and
              one  sink. The design must be routed before you use this parame-
              ter.

              Default: true

       -updateTiming {true|false}
              Controls whether to eco* commands recompute timing. If true, the
              eco* commands recompute timing. If false, the  commands  do  not
              recompute  timing,  and us can later use report_timing to recom-
              pute timing.

              Default: true

Examples
              * The following command does  not  legalize  placement  whenever
                ecoAddRepeater or ecoChangeCell are used:

                setEcoMode -refinePlace false

              * The  following command resets the -honorDontTouch parameter to
                its default value:

                setEcoMode -reset -honorDontTouch

              * The following command  resets  all  setEcoMode  parameters  to
                their default values:

                setEcoMode -reset

Related Information
              * ecoAddRepeater

              * ecoChangeCell

              * ecoDeleteRepeater

              * getEcoMode

              * refinePlace

              * report_timing

              * setOptMode

